snippet.textDisplay:
Enabling mouse/keyboard on Xbox is not a really good thing. Yes, there are already 3rd party applications for PS4/Xbox to enable mouse and keyboard and maybe Microsoft is trying to get in money with an ol'  " 1st party is more reliable" shtick but, overall, it can seriously boost one's performance compared to other players on the same system that do use the controller.
I mean, I wouldn't want to feel like I was at a disadvantage by using the controller's designed and provided by the manufacturer and for witch game developers developed the games.

TL;Dr - mouse and keyboard on consoles is already a thing but it sucks for the console gaming community
